      "title": "Kimbrough Memorial Stadium",
      "score": 0.0992187678383222,
      "text": "Kimbrough Memorial Stadium\nKimbrough Memorial Stadium is a stadium in Canyon, Texas. It is owned by Canyon Independent School District, and is primarily primarily used for American football. It is the home stadium for Canyon High School and Randall High School of Canyon Independent School District, and is the former home of West Texas A&M University. The stadium holds 20,000 people and was built in 1959. It was originally called Buffalo Bowl on Canyon Hill but was renamed Kimbrough Memorial Stadium in 1971 in honor of the late West Texas State University football coach and athletic director Frank Kimbrough.",
      "score_breakdown": {
        "dense": 0.05133706805646527,
        "graph": 0.05222074957848143,
        "fact": 0.3687810368914791
      }
