      "node_id": "chunk:saulkrasti_municipality_0",
      "passage_index": 12,
      "title": "Saulkrasti Municipality",
      "score": 0.09198231176760521,
      "text": "Saulkrasti Municipality\nSaulkrasti Municipality () is a municipality in Vidzeme, Latvia. The municipality was formed in 2009 by reorganization of Saulkrasti town with its countryside territory, with the administrative centre being Saulkrasti. In 2010 Saulkrasti parish was created from the countryside territory of Saulkrasti town.",
      "score_breakdown": {
        "dense": 0.050035106074093234,
        "graph": 0.05068444712205701,
        "fact": 0.3283844619349123
      }
    },
    {
      "node_id": "chunk:canyon_texas_0",
      "passage_index": 16,
      "title": "Canyon, Texas",
      "score": 0.08759066880884134,
      "text": "Canyon, Texas\nCanyon is a city in, and the county seat of, Randall County, Texas, United States. The population was 13,303 at the 2010 census. It is part of the Amarillo, Texas, metropolitan statistical area. Canyon is the home of West Texas A&M University and Panhandle–Plains Historical Museum, and the world-famous outdoor musical drama \"Texas\".",
      "score_breakdown": {
        "dense": 0.05018918158818401,
        "graph": 0.048538145864329495,
